Author: Wan C (2015)
Qualifications: Fractionation was combined with mass spectrometry from five diverse animal species to predict co-complex protein interactions conserved across metazoa using an integrative computational scoring procedure along with an SVM approach. The significant data set of 16655 PPI, was derived from a set of more than 1M interactions by examining a ROC curve of predicted interactions against reference annotated complexes at a 67.5% cumulative precision.

Author: Liu Y (2024)
Qualifications: Within each experiment, reporter intensity values (protein peak areas) are normalized by calculating the median for each sample, equalizing the medians across all samples, and then subtracting the AP-MS results from the negative control (GFP-empty). Hits where all three replicates show a positive value after this subtraction are considered potential MECP2 interactors. The score represents the log2-transformed average of the adjusted binding intensity from three replicates.
